{
  "texts": [
    "For each model, we track a summary statistic over time: the number of happy agents in Schelling, and the number of active (i.e.",
    "Alive and Pregnant) agents in the predator-prey ecosystem.",
    "Reusing the same ramification branches as in training would offer little new information, since different stochastic branches from the same state tend to produce very similar macroscopic trajectories.",
    "Instead, we generate a fresh ensemble of main-branch simulations (100 independent runs) beyond the training horizon.",
    "We then compute the symmetric mean absolute percentage error (sMAPE) between the mean ground-truth trajectory and the mean surrogate-predicted trajectory across this ensemble, providing a quantitative measure of the surrogate's ability to capture oscillations and steady-state behavior truly out-of-sample.Experimental set-up."
  ]
}